dc_title_s: Marine Protected Areas, Hopkins Marine Laboratory, California, 2000
dc_description_s: This polygon shapefile depicts the (estimated) boundary of the Hopkins Marine Laboratory reserve located in Pacific Grove, California on the Monterey Peninsula. This layer is part of a collection of data created by the California Department of Fish and Game.To identify the approximate area of the Hopkins Marine Lab reserve for mapping other kelp harvest areas and no-take MPAs along the Montery coast.
dc_publisher_s: California. Department of Fish and Game. Marine Resources Region
dc_creator_sm: California. Department of Fish and Game. Marine Resources Region
